The paper deals with solving combinatorial optimization problems using linear programming and rounding techniques, which are commonly studied in the subfield of theoretical computer science known as approximation algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the use of stochastic-coordinate-descent methods, which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and numerical optimization (cs.NA). The experiments involve solving problems such as vertex cover, independent set, and multiway-cut, which are classic problems in the subfield of discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.CC).
